It's a great little RealGood Stuff Co. with some very fresh daily made to go lunches such as sushi and lunch boxes. It has a wide selection of Japanese products at an affordable price.

Went to Real Good Stuff Co. on Wells and had the best experience. Coming into the store, I didn’t realize that they didn’t take cash. But the woman working was the absolute sweetest person!! I told her I could go back and get my card, but she insisted that it was on her. I was so shocked! I then insisted that I go back to get my card, but she made sure that I was taken care of and gave it to me for free. RGS has the best and most caring workers — their noyofroyo is also next level — and I would recommend this place over any other place in chicago!!!
Great value. Delicious food. Quick service. Can’t go wrong. Only con is the acai bowl base but I have yet to find a place in Chicago that can get that right.
First time trying a juice here and it was really great! The woman working was super helpful and recommended a green drink that was surprisingly delicious! A bit pricey but I’ll definitely be back.
Love the noyo and yummy bowls
Neat space, good service.  Awesome smoothies and -DO NOT- skip the avocado toast!

Omg where to start....... I had the Best Seller Salad and the Jucille Ball juice. Both were very good. The chicken in the salad was so flavorful as well as the kale which wasn’t raw it seems like it had been steamed or something at some point. The juice was interesting with that hint of spice from the cayenne.  I highly recommend you give it a try!
Delicious food with high quality ingredients and the staff are friendly and helpful! Highly recommend the pesto toast!
Solid smoothies, marginally over priced but a great place to get a healthy breakfast!

This is the place for NoYo-FroYo.  It is so good and great for those who can't handle dairy or choose the vegan lifestyle. The vanilla lemon has such a light creamy taste and pairs so well with fresh fruit and coconut flakes.  For a special treat try the CBD infused juice shots.  They also have some amazing bowls, sandwiches, juices and salads.  Minimal space inside to sit and eat, so be prepared to do take out.

I love this chain in the city ! My favorite thing to get their is their Michael Bowlton but I’ve tried other things as well and it’s always yummy! Also they always seem to have such kind and friendly staff!

Delicious foods but depending who prepared your bowl they are either generous or stingy as hell. I'd add a pic of the bowl I paid for with greens. I swear I got like 3 leaves of greens in my bowl. I litterly go there 3/4 times a week. They are so inconsistent it's annoying. I can't call to complain because they don't answer the phone.
Acai bowls are delicious. FANTASTIC juice selection. Yummmy!!

Real Good has so many tasty food options! I LOVE the vegan chocolate chip cookies, the breakfast burritos and the overnight oats (which they sadly don't sell anymore). The reason for two stars is because I've encountered a staff member (woman with red hair) on a few occasions who has been short with me and I'm not sure why. I'm not a sensitive person but I can pick up on nasty attitudes pretty quickly.  I normally would get something from them in the mornings because I work in the area. I've watched how this employee kindly address other people in line before me yet be short with me. In addition to that, there was a time when I was getting the overnight oats pretty regularly. Other employees (who have been incredibly nice and helpful) would offer fruit and granola and it was the same price every time. One day I ordered the overnight oats from this rude person, ordered it the same way, and she charged me an extra dollar for granola. I told her that I hadn't paid for extra granola in the past. Her snippy response was "well they should've been charging you."  Another time, I was asking about hot food items with the dumb assumption that she would apply good customer service and assist me with some options. Nope. Instead she turned her back to me and started working on something else and I was left awkwardly standing there to just figure it out on my own.  I've noticed that I get anxious about going into Real Good because I don't want to deal with this person. So I don't bother going there anymore. She's either overworked or misplacing her frustrations or she's just a genuinely nasty person. I'm not spending anymore of my hard earned money at this location.  And just to reiterate, I've encountered other employees there who have been so kind, helpful, and nice to talk to. I'm not 100% familiar with the items they offer. So helpful, kind employees do go a long way.
Healthy juices and cute interior!
(Translated by Google) $ 13 for a smothie? to get me mad once  (Original) $13 for a smothie? hahahahaha fool me once

“Cold pressed” juice AKA overpriced juice. Small storefront with half the drinks you order in prepackaged bottles. The concept doesn’t make sense to me but it always seems likes there is people in this place. When I was told $18 for two bottles of juice I was pretty much done ever coming back. 2 stars for friendly service.
I love this place! Best vibes and the “No-Yo” (dairy free frozen yogurt) has become a staple in my diet... I’m obsessed

Save your money This is the 3rd time I've visited a Real Good since I've come to Chicago  Pros: Dairy free  Cons: The quality isn't consistent Not actually organic The staff never seems excited about working there Overpriced in an attempt to be trendy

I drive for Uber eats, had  delivery from here, decided to come back & try the fruity pebble bowl OMG!!!!! Delicious!!! The staff were very professional & happy spirit! And extremely helpful explaining the ingredients Definitely My New hangout!!!!!
Good but overpriced

“Real Terrible Juice” Terrible juices, terrible smoothies, terrible service, terrible prices.This is not the place to get your health fix this summer or ever. Also your branding sucks. What overgrown manchild is in charge of this business ?  Thumbs down.

I have to say, I used to be their number one customer at the location in Streeterville so I’m disappointed to be leaving this review. A girl named Lily made the best smoothies and bowls for me every morning. I had a great experience daily. However, after she left I noticed the management changed.I’ve had one to  many terrible experiences ever since. I’ve gotten SICK from their smoothies and juices constantly.The management is poor. I have traveled to Old town, Lakeview and Southport. Completely disappointed.Streeterville is the closest to my condo. After all this time I find out that They’re NON-ORGANIC after being lied to by Real good staff and I’m taking this up with Whole Foods! The staff is UNSANITARY also highly unprofessional. Total disappointment. I have spent so much money at real good and officially will never return! Officially giving that new Goddess place a chance. Disappointed!

Great juices, smoothies, and quick bites. In -nd-out kind of place. Avocado toasts, chia pudding, etc. Food 5/5- I had the seasonal avocado toast and it was great. Service 5/5- Very friendly, helpful and professional staff. Good vibes. Everything was made in a snap. Cleanliness/ atmosphere 5/5- Clean, cozy, minimalistic approach. Love it! You have some seating inside and about 8 outdoor seats to enjoy your food as you people watch on the sidewalk.
Seriously the nicest people & everything was delicious! I did not want to leave 😍

My favorite juice and smoothie place anywhere and the food is fantastic as well. Names of everything are hilarious. Best staff you can find anywhere. Get your health fix here. Wish there were 20 more in the city.

Stopped in for some real food after a day of traveling and was very impressed! I had a delicious grain bowl and the service was awesome! I also grabbed a "Juice Springsteen" on the way out, which was fresh and refreshing! Great atmosphere and vegan options.
So happy! Great find!
